{
  "stem": "18778.5",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 14.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "It was husband and wife, each one a teacher, each one born in the '40s, so they were not of the Hitler generation.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "They had two daughters.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And they invited us to their home and they came to see us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And there were flowers in our rooms from them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And they are the loveliest people.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "I'm still in touch with them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "They were very gracious to us and joined the program.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "This was voluntary.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "There were people there that didn't come out of the walls while we were there, you know.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "But it was important.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "I spoke in several schools, in a-- in a Catholic school, an elementary school, and in a high school.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Many of the children had been prepared by reading literature about the Holocaust or leading-- reading stories.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "They asked intelligent questions.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they were very concerned whether we blame them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was a universal question, do you blame us?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We can't tell young people that we blame them, you know.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I think they felt relieved.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And since this was the one and only invitation that our town extended, simply because they just invited everybody who survived, because it was a small Jewish community in the first place, they too had their trepidations about how we would receive them and how they would receive us, and whether there would be animosity or whatever.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it doesn't happen.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It really doesn't happen.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I've heard from so many people who've gone over with a chip on their shoulder or who go over who say, well, we'll take what we can get from them, but we don't really want to go, or as somebody expressed in our group, my heart said yes and my brain said no, you know.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you come away feeling better.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
